      "options": {
        "content": "Paste an exact value into **Correlation ID regex** or keep `.*` to browse recent requests.\\n\\n1. If you control the caller, send `X-Correlation-Id` on the request.\\n2. Start with **Request Entry Logs** and click **View trace** on a row that contains `trace_id`.\\n3. Use **Correlated Tool + Security Events** to see follow-on activity under the same `correlation_id`.\\n4. Gateway-only rejections can still appear only in Kong logs and will not have a backend trace.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "How To Follow One Request",
      "type": "text"
    },
